defaultQ133default 
defaultNiadefault defaultGriffithdefault:default I would like to ask a very fundamental question. You are seeking out a fuel that will contribute to our emissions problem, not only in its extraction but in its use as a fuel. Really, we should be thinking of ways to reduce the amount of emissions that we produce. Given that this is a new venture and there is a lot of investment going in, how can you justify the fact that that investment is going into using and extracting a fossil fuel and making it available, rather than being invested in carbon-neutral energies? 
defaultGerwyndefault Williams:default May I answer that? We need a bridging fuel in this country, and we need it fairly quickly. Yesterday, 38.7% of electricity was generated from gas in the 
defaultUK
